## The Powerhouse of Enterprise: Java
Java is a high-level, class-based, **object-oriented** programming language designed to have as few implementation dependencies as possible.
Unlike Python, which is interpreted, Java is a **compiled** language—but with a twist. It compiles code into **Bytecode**, which is then executed by the **Java Virtual Machine (JVM)**.
This makes Java significantly faster than Python for heavy computational tasks while remaining cross-platform.

