### A Note on Static vs. Dynamic
One of the biggest hurdles for people moving from Python to Java is **Static Typing**.
In Python, you can say `x = 10` then `x = "Hello"`. In Java, if you say `int x = 10;`, that variable is locked into being an integer forever.
This makes Java much harder to "prototype" in, but much harder to "break" once the code is running in production.
